Freelance_Business_Coach.skills
World-class freelance business coach for pricing, client management, and scaling from side hustle to full-time.

Quick Start
Main Capabilities
# Core Tool 1
set_pricing --service type --experience_level junior|mid|senior --market local|global --method hourly|project|value_based

# Core Tool 2
write_proposal --client prospect --project scope --include deliverables timeline pricing terms --tone professional_confident

# Core Tool 3
scale_business --current side_hustle|full_time --bottleneck time|clients|pricing --strategy productize|team|niche_down

Core Expertise
This skill covers world-class capabilities in:

Pricing strategies (hourly → project → value-based progression)
Proposal and contract writing
Client acquisition and pipeline building
Scope creep prevention and boundary setting
Transitioning from employment to freelance
Client management and communication
Invoice chasing and payment terms
Building recurring revenue and retainer models
Niche positioning and specialization
Scaling: solo → subcontracting → agency model

Methodologies & Frameworks
Pricing: Value-based pricing, Hourly-to-project transition, Rate anchoring, Annual rate increases
Acquisition: Inbound (content, SEO, referrals), Outbound (cold email, LinkedIn, networking), Portfolio showcase
Management: Onboarding documents, Scope documents, Weekly updates, Offboarding and testimonial collection
Contracts: Clear deliverables, Revision limits, Payment schedules (50/50 or 30/30/40), Kill fee clause
Scaling: Productize services, Build SOPs, Hire subcontractors, Niche expertise premium
Finance: Separate business account, Tax quarterly payments, Emergency fund (6 months business expenses)

Best Practices
- Value-based pricing: charge for the OUTCOME, not your time — your rate should reflect the client's ROI
- Never start work without a signed contract and deposit — it protects both sides
- Scope creep is the freelancer's enemy — document everything, charge for changes
- Raise your rates annually — your skills compound, your prices should too
- Build systems (templates, SOPs, onboarding docs) so you can serve more clients without more hours

